{"kind": "page", "url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "path": "en/network-config.md", "title": "Enterprise network configuration", "description": "Configure Claude Code for enterprise environments with proxy servers, custom Certificate Authorities (CA), and mutual Transport Layer Security (mTLS) authentication.", "description_source": "llms.txt", "content_hash": "f67af899f00e7b08f06e2f6a33178b81c1fc0babf3d5505973e7eecfc0a4204c", "volatile": false}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "fe14377ae54a0bee", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#overview", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "All environment variables shown on this page can also be configured in `settings.json`."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Configure Claude Code for enterprise environments with proxy servers, custom Certificate Authorities (CA), and mutual Transport Layer Security (mTLS) authentication.\n\nClaude Code supports various enterprise network and security configurations through environment variables. This includes routing traffic through corporate proxy servers, trusting custom Certificate Authorities (CA), and authenticating with mutual Transport Layer Security (mTLS) certificates for enhanced security.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "2bd1ec77aa3976ab", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#environment-variables", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "# HTTPS proxy (recommended)\nexport HTTPS_PROXY=https://proxy.example.com:8080\n\n# HTTP proxy (if HTTPS not available)\nexport HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.example.com:8080\n\n# Bypass proxy for specific requests - space-separated format\nexport NO_PROXY=\"localhost 192.168.1.1 example.com .example.com\"\n# Bypass proxy for specific requests - comma-separated format\nexport NO_PROXY=\"localhost,192.168.1.1,example.com,.example.com\"\n# Bypass proxy for all requests\nexport NO_PROXY=\"*\"", "preceding_paragraph": "Claude Code respects standard proxy environment variables:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "9f6803a3e6457bc5", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#environment-variables", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "Claude Code does not support SOCKS proxies."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#environment-variables", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "environment-variables", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > Proxy configuration > Environment variables", "level": 3, "position": 2, "text": "Claude Code respects standard proxy environment variables:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#proxy-configuration", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "d9eecc41992b4930", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#basic-authentication", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "export HTTPS_PROXY=http://username:password@proxy.example.com:8080", "preceding_paragraph": "If your proxy requires basic authentication, include credentials in the proxy URL:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "7d27e974125bebd3", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#basic-authentication", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "warning", "text": "Avoid hardcoding passwords in scripts. Use environment variables or secure credential storage instead."}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "7b02dd93a4ca743e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#basic-authentication", "position": 1, "callout_kind": "tip", "text": "For proxies requiring advanced authentication (NTLM, Kerberos, etc.), consider using an LLM Gateway service that supports your authentication method."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#basic-authentication", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "basic-authentication", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > Proxy configuration > Basic authentication", "level": 3, "position": 3, "text": "If your proxy requires basic authentication, include credentials in the proxy URL:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#proxy-configuration", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#proxy-configuration", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "proxy-configuration", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > Proxy configuration", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "b0bdfafc43c946c3", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#ca-certificate-store", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "System CA store integration requires the native Claude Code binary distribution. When running on the Node.js runtime, the system CA store is not merged automatically. In that case, set `NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS=/path/to/ca-cert.pem` to trust an enterprise root CA."}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7871e5de5609426d", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#ca-certificate-store", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "export CLAUDE_CODE_CERT_STORE=bundled", "preceding_paragraph": "To trust only the bundled Mozilla CA set:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "13a13ce48fc97eae", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#ca-certificate-store", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "export CLAUDE_CODE_CERT_STORE=system", "preceding_paragraph": "To trust only the OS certificate store:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "341c302e403b9d95", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#ca-certificate-store", "position": 1, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "`CLAUDE_CODE_CERT_STORE` has no dedicated `settings.json` schema key. Set it via the `env` block in `~/.claude/settings.json` or directly in the process environment."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#ca-certificate-store", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "ca-certificate-store", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > CA certificate store", "level": 2, "position": 4, "text": "By default, Claude Code trusts both its bundled Mozilla CA certificates and your operating system's certificate store. Enterprise TLS-inspection proxies such as CrowdStrike Falcon and Zscaler work without additional configuration when their root certificate is installed in the OS trust store.\n\n`CLAUDE_CODE_CERT_STORE` accepts a comma-separated list of sources. Recognized values are `bundled` for the Mozilla CA set shipped with Claude Code and `system` for the operating system trust store. The default is `bundled,system`.\n\nTo trust only the bundled Mozilla CA set:\n\nTo trust only the OS certificate store:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "34b9cb15943489f2", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#custom-ca-certificates", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "export NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS=/path/to/ca-cert.pem", "preceding_paragraph": "If your enterprise environment uses a custom CA, configure Claude Code to trust it directly:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#custom-ca-certificates", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "custom-ca-certificates", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > Custom CA certificates", "level": 2, "position": 5, "text": "If your enterprise environment uses a custom CA, configure Claude Code to trust it directly:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "d622fab643d26a9c", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#mtls-authentication", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "# Client certificate for authentication\nexport CLAUDE_CODE_CLIENT_CERT=/path/to/client-cert.pem\n\n# Client private key\nexport CLAUDE_CODE_CLIENT_KEY=/path/to/client-key.pem\n\n# Optional: Passphrase for encrypted private key\nexport CLAUDE_CODE_CLIENT_KEY_PASSPHRASE=\"your-passphrase\"", "preceding_paragraph": "For enterprise environments requiring client certificate authentication:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md#mtls-authentication", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/network-config.md", "anchor": "mtls-authentication", "breadcrumb": "Enterprise network configuration > mTLS authentication", "level": 2, "position": 6, "text": "For enterprise environments requiring client certificate authentication:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
